title: Prince Avenue Christian still tops in football Power Ratings
text:
More Weather AJ Reynolds/Staff, @ajreynoldsphoto 
Prince Avenue Christian players take the field during the GHSA high school football game between Prince Avenue Christian and Athens Christian on Friday, Sept. 18, 2015, in Athens, Ga. (AJ Reynolds/Staff, @ajreynoldsphoto) Prince Avenue Christian still tops in football Power Ratings By Nicole Saavedra published Tuesday, October 20, 2015 close Jefferson, Prince Avenue Christian hold on to spots in high school football polls Prince Avenue Christian sits atop the Georgia High School Association’s Class A Private Football Power Ratings following a 42-14 win over Towns County Friday. The ratings were released on Tuesday. 
The Wolverines (8-0, 6-0 in Region 8-A) are off this week, and will host Lakeview Academy at 7:30 p.m. Oct. 30. 
Athens Academy (6-1, 4-1) is ranked eighth and will visit Providence Christian at 7:30 p.m. Friday. Athens Christian (4-4, 3-3) is ranked 16th. The Eagles will play at Lakeview Academy Friday. Commerce (4-3, 3-2) is sixth in Class A Public. The Tigers will visit Towns County at 7:30 p.m. Friday. GHSA Power Ratings 1 Prince Avenue Christian; 8-A; 8-0; 15.32 2. Mt.
